🔐 System Security Audit — Steps

STEP 1: System Information
• Press Windows + R
• Type: msinfo32
• Note OS version, system type
• Windows 11, 64-bit, Intel i5
• Secure Boot enabled
• Secure Boot improves system security

STEP 2: Check Windows Updates
• Open Settings → Windows Update
• Click Check for updates
• Updates pending, restart required
• Updates fix vulnerabilities

STEP 3: Check Firewall Status
• Search Windows Defender Firewall
• Open settings
• Firewall managed by Kaspersky
• Third-party firewall active
• Provides network protection

STEP 4: Check Antivirus
• Open Windows Security
• Virus & Threat Protection
• Real-time protection ON
• No threats detected
• Kaspersky antivirus active

STEP 5: Check Account Security
• Settings → Accounts → Sign-in options
• Password and PIN enabled
• Windows Hello available
• Strong authentication improves security

STEP 6: Check Installed Applications
• Settings → Apps → Installed apps
• Look for unknown or cracked software
• No suspicious apps found
• Unknown apps increase malware risk

STEP 7: Check Startup Programs
• Press Ctrl + Shift + Esc
• Go to Startup tab
• Disable unnecessary apps
• Improves performance and security

STEP 8: Check Network Security
• Settings → Network & Internet
• Check Wi-Fi status
• Network profile = Public
• Public network limits access
• Improves security in untrusted networks

STEP 9: Check Browser Security
• Open browser settings
• Privacy & Security
• Safe Browsing ON
• Remove unknown extensions
• Protects from phishing/malware

STEP 10: Check Data Backup
• Open Backup settings
• Check OneDrive / external backup
• Backup not configured
• Risk of data loss

STEP 11: Risk Assessment
• Files → Data loss → No backup → High → Enable backup
• System → Malware → Unknown apps → High → Remove apps
• Network → Hacking → Public → Medium → Use private
• Account → Unauthorized access → Weak password → High → Strong password

STEP 12: Security Recommendations
• Enable firewall and antivirus
• Keep system updated
• Use strong passwords
• Avoid unknown downloads
• Avoid phishing links
• Practice safe browsing

STEP 13: Result
• Audit completed
• Vulnerabilities identified
• Security improvements suggested
  
